dct_title_s: Eastern Turkey in Asia. Bayazid, sheet 13. Series I.D.W.O. no. 1522
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Includes an index to adjoining sheets, and a glossary. "Lith. at the Intell. Div. War Office, Aug. 1901. Partially revised to Aug. 1916." Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Some sheets from this set were revised and issued by War Office. Geographical Section. General Staff, published as G.S.G.S. no. 1522, 1522a. Series covers Mesopotamia and eastern Anatolian parts of Ottoman Empire. "Compiled at the Intelligence Division, War Office by Major F.R. Maunsell, R.A. from Russian 5 Verst Surveys. Turco-Persion Frontier Map 1913-14, Lieut. Col. Picot's Reconnaissance in Azerbijan 1895 and Major F.R. Maunsell's R.A. Reconnaissance 1900." Partially revised to Aug 1916. With a glossary. Set is complete, see index. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. no. 1522. Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division. I.D.W.O. no. 1522.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. Intelligence Division
